i hardly ever get angry, but this whole dance thing is really really pissing me off...
if you don't wanna be there, don't.

if it's not where you see yourself doing what you want, or what will better you and you can't get along with anyone...why are you there? 

its bad attitudes thats ruining dance, not miss c, bad fucking attitudes.

I can't walk into the studio without wondering how i'm going to be greeted, if I recieve any...

i'm so happy that we are so mature that we can think about other peoples perspectives... i've tried, i've walked on fuckin eggshells, kept my mouth shut and just been there, tried lightenin things up... but no...

so i say fuck it... i'm gonna go there and enjoy... i may not be a true dancer... i dont go to classes in the city and i don't have the best skills in dance...but dammit i try, and i try to make it an enjoyable thing for everyone...

i can't be 18 anymore... i'm graduating college next year, i'm going to grad school after that...we all grow up ( age/numbers wise anyway)...

i used to care about the backlash that saying even this little bit might incur, and i am not talking about everyone at dance,if you have it in your mind that this refers to you... maybe it does...and consider why it may. 

i'm not talking down to anyone... ... but life is bigger than just one person. 


and i want it known that if i didn't care, this wouldn't bother me so much.

but you prob dont care about that... what do you care about? being depressed, pissed, screwed, what? do you care about yourself? dog bites, scratches, and other "accidents" included...
i dont know what your life has been like...but i do know its possible to rise above it...and not just for show, or when someone bends over backwards to make you happy, but genuinely. 

and i am not telling you how to live life...i just wish you would live the great one your meant to, and i'll be here.

so sick... still waitin on this ovary thing....and now i have a cold/laringitis on top of it...

i realized last night just how out of it I am... I don't listen to hip hop/r & b/dance/techno/basically anything relatively new. 
well i do listen to R&b, but the originals, not today's best...

i feel old. i know its just me, and the fact that i am getting older...but i feel it... my mom called me n dave old farts last night... i was like gee thanks, i'm sick, i have no voice, i just killed myself to perfomr for miss c, and you're makin fun of me...no...

the show... didnt wanna do it, but it always winds up being entertaining... of course the men/dads were the funniest...i messed up in both dances, due to hacking fits followed by sharp pains...and in cotton eyed joe miss c put the two smallest children next to me...for me to keep an eye on them... one kid would not move and the other kid was going wild... practically ran right off stage... i had to grab her at the last second and pull her back onto stage and dance in front of her with her pushing at the back of my legs...then dave took me to get food and mom n dad went out to eat, and me n dave went home and sat around...

i have so much shit to do... next year is going to be crazy...i hate life...but i love it...
if anyone knows where i can go to get a nice vintagey/used electric bass, or just bass guitar... lemme know... cuz i wanna get it for dave for his 21st/one year anniversary/xmas....

hey i'm gonna be 21... any suggestions for a party?

( this entry took a long time to type due to constant hacking up of yuck)

hmm... i havent drank in a while..mebe tonight me n dave can work somethin out for once we get home from this concert thing...hrmmm....

ok well... i hafta go spit this shit out...

ooh oooh... i'm going to see eric clapton at MSG for my bday!!! june 30th...me n dave...yay!!!!someone famous is opening for him, i'm so bad with names... something and the family band...dave knows...

sigh, we smother eachother, its great...

ok, off to cough up my vocal chords
